CNCP v1 23369
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13436: `<option>` without `value` attr won't have `selected` attr in the SSR output",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:20:50.143571+00:00",
  "text": "`<option>` without `value` attr won't have `selected` attr in the SSR output\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.16\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#__SSR__\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Switch to the `SSR` table on right pane\n2. Checkout the line 30:\n   ```js\n           : _ssrLooseEqual($setup.theValue, null))) ? \" selected\" : \"\"\n   ```\n\n### What is expected?\n\nComparing `$setup.theValue` with the text of `<option>` that is `possibleValue` in `v-for` like browser.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nComparing with `null` causing `_ssrLooseEqual()` always being evaluated to `false`, so only the first `<option>` of `<select>` will be appeared as selected before hydrate.\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nThe reproduction is taken from https://github.com/vuejs/core/issues/12395",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: ssr",
    "has workaround",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
